And where does he now exist? Is this gentle and lovely being lost for ever? Has this mind, so replete with ideas, imaginations fanciful and magnificent, which formed a world, whose existence depended on the life of its creator;\u8212\'97has this mind perished? Does it now only exist in my memory? No, it is not thus; your form so divinely wrought, and beaming with beauty, has decayed, but your spirit still visits and consoles your unhappy friend.}
{\lang1033\par}\pard\plain \s0\sl276\slmult1\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\faauto\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\kerning1\strike0\ulc0\cf1\rtlch\af7\afs22\alang1081\ai0\ab0\ltrch\hich\af4\afs22\alang2057\ai0\aulnone\ab0\dbch\af7\langfe2052\loch\f4\fs22\lang2057\i0\ulnone\b0\sl276\slmult1\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0\brdrt\brdrnone\brdrl\brdrnone\brdrb\brdrnone\brdrr\brdrnone

